|Example.Language=Russian
|Example.Text=Чиновники умывают руки - разрешение они дали, а отслеживать, как медицинское средство продается и используется, в их компетенцию не входит.
|Example.Gloss=Officials wash hands - authorization they gave,and to track how remedy sells and is used, into their competence not enter.
|Example.English translation=Officials are washing their hands - they gave the authorization, but tracking the way a remedy is sold and used doesn't fall within their competence.
|Example.Provenance=medrelax.narod.ru/pribor.htm
|Example.Comments=The set expression "to wash one's hands" is used in Russian to denote reluctance of a person to participate in smth bad or illegal, to emphasize he/she is innocent. It originates from the old tradition to wash one's hands and say loudly "I'm innocent" to prove he/she has nothing to do with a certain criminal act.
}}{{Example
